dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Marienburg, sheet K-13. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Marienburg, Germany. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany 1:25,000. German General Staff 1909-31; Germany, 1:100,000, German General Staff, sheet 27, 1933; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 32-27, 1935; 32-28, 1937; 33-27, 1932 and 33-28, 1931. Road classification in Poland and Danzig Free State based on British Intelligence Reports, 1943. Map states location as Germany though the map actually depicts Poland.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
